title: My first visit to Europe:
author: Dickinson, Andrew
snippet: My house is No. 2 Holly Terrace, Highgate Hill; and there is an omnibus from Tottenham Court Road, corner of Oxford street, at ten minutes past five, which passes the door. There are also other omnibuses from the same place to Kentish Town, about a mile short, about every quarter of an hour, if you should feel disposed to come up earlier, to see something of the country.
